Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State has expressed his expectation that President Muhammadu Buhari will guide the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in the decision on zoning of the 2023 presidential ticket of the party.
The Ogun Governor during a visit to the President at the State House, Abuja, expressed optimism that President Buhari guide the APC in deciding zoning towards ensuring equity and justice in the party. Governor Abiodun added that the decision of the APC on zoning will be made public after it has been ratified by the National Executive Council.
the governor ked a broad delegation to the State House, Abuja, to thank President Buhari for his recent visit to Ogun State.  The delegation included former Governor Olusegun Osoba, Chairman of the Council of Obas, Oba Babatunde Ajayi; former Deputy Governor Salimot Badru; and a renowned industrialist, Chief Sulaiman Adegunwa.
